This paper deals with natural language understanding tasks, specifically entity tracking in procedural text, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also explores the use of pre-trained transformer networks, which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper involves training models to predict entity tracking, which can be considered a form of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses state-of-the-art techniques to achieve strong results, which is a common theme in neural networks (cs.NE).
